Engine-contract parity fixtures
================================

Each <name>.json file in this directory captures one HeadroomEngine.on_request
input→output pair in a language-neutral, byte-exact format for cross-engine
parity checking.

Fixture schema
--------------

{
  "name":              "<descriptive slug>",
  "provider":          "<Provider enum value, e.g. 'anthropic'>",
  "flavor":            "<Flavor enum value, e.g. 'messages'>",
  "auth_mode":         "<payg | oauth | subscription — for documentation only>",
  "headers":           { "<header-name>": "<header-value>", ... },
  "session_key":       "<hex string>",
  "config_optimize":   true | false,
  "raw_body_b64":      "<base64-encoded raw request bytes>",
  "expected_body_b64": "<base64-encoded golden output bytes>",
  "passthrough":       true | false,
  "passthrough_reason": "<bypass_header | compression_disabled | no_messages | null>",
  "recorded_at":       "<ISO-8601 UTC timestamp>"
}

raw_body_b64 / expected_body_b64 are standard base64 (RFC 4648 §4) with no
line wrapping. The Rust D2 replayer decodes them with standard::base64::decode
and compares byte-for-byte.

Passthrough fixtures (Chunks 3)
--------------------------------
These fixtures exercise the passthrough path (should_compress=False). The
expected_body_b64 is byte-identical to raw_body_b64 because HeadroomEngine
returns ctx.raw_body unchanged. Headers are chosen to cover all three AuthMode
classifications (payg, oauth, subscription) and all bypass mechanisms
(bypass_header, compression_disabled, no_messages) so invariant I10 is
exercised on the classification path even when compression does not run.

Compression fixtures (Chunk 4+)
---------------------------------
Golden fixtures that capture a real TransformPipeline output are deferred to
Chunk 4, when the real pipeline is wired into HeadroomEngine. At that point,
run:

    .venv/bin/python scripts/record_engine_fixtures.py --mode compress

to produce them. Do NOT fake compression output as golden — only real pipeline
output is valid here.
